Lib9: Plan 9 Compatibility Library

A Plan 9 C library compatibility layer for TaijiOS, adapted from Inferno OS.
Lib9 enables programs using Plan 9 conventions to compile and run on modern
POSIX systems.

OVERVIEW

Lib9 provides Plan 9 C library functions for TaijiOS:

    String formatting
        print, fprint, sprint, snprint, seprint, smprint
        fmtinstall, dostfmt, dorfmt

    Utility functions
        cleanname, argv0, exits, sysfatal
        tokenize, getfields, strdup, strecpy

    Unicode support
        utflen, utfnlen, utfrrune, utfrune, utfecpy
        runestrchr, runestrlen, runetype
        runeseprint, runesmprint, runesnprint

    9P protocol
        convD2M, convM2D, convM2S, convS2M
        fcallfmt

    Directory operations
        dirstat, dirwstat, create

QUICK START

Build and install:

    mk
    mk install

Use in your code:

    #include <u.h>
    #include <libc.h>

DOCUMENTATION

See man/ directory for manual pages.

COMPONENTS

lib9/                - Core library source
lib9/posix/          - POSIX-specific implementations
include/             - Public API headers

REQUIREMENTS

    - Plan 9 compilers (9c/9l/9a) or GCC
    - POSIX system (Linux, BSD, macOS)

BUILD

    mk                 - Build liblib9.a
    mk install         - Install to $ROOT/lib
    mk clean           - Clean build artifacts

Binary: $ROOT/lib/liblib9.a

CONFIGURATION

The mkfile selects platform-specific implementations:
POSIX (Linux, BSD, macOS)
    errstr-posix, getuser-posix, getwd-posix

EXAMPLES

String formatting:

    char buf[256];
    snprint(buf, sizeof(buf), "Value: %d", 42);

File operations:

    Dir *d = dirstat("/path/to/file");
    if(d) {
        print("File size: %lld\n", d->length);
        free(d);
    }
